quran[32]{c,v,t}:
  25,21,"Those who do not expect to meet Us say, ‚ÄúIf only the angels were sent down to us, or we could see our Lord!‚ÄĚ They have certainly been carried away by their arrogance and have entirely exceeded all limits"
  25,22,"ňĻButňļ on the Day they will see the angels, there will be no good news for the wicked, who will cry, ‚ÄúKeep away! Away ňĻfrom usňļ!‚ÄĚ"
  25,23,"Then We will turn to whatever ňĻgoodňļ deeds they did, reducing them to scattered dust"
  25,24,ňĻButňļ on that Day the residents of Paradise will have the best settlement and the finest place to rest
  25,25,"ňĻWatch forňļ the Day the heavens will burst with clouds, and the angels will be sent down in successive ranks"
  25,26,True authority on that Day will belong ňĻonlyňļ to the Most Compassionate.¬†And it will be a hard day for the disbelievers
  25,27,"And ňĻbeware ofňļ the Day the wrongdoer will bite his nails ňĻin regretňļ and say, ‚ÄúOh! I wish I had followed the Way along with the Messenger"
  25,28,Woe to me! I wish I had never taken so-and-so as a close friend
  25,29,It was he who truly made me stray from the Reminder after it had reached me.‚ÄĚ And Satan has always betrayed humanity
  25,30,"The Messenger has cried, ‚ÄúO my Lord! My people have indeed received this Quran with neglect.‚ÄĚ"
  25,31,"Similarly, We made enemies for every prophet from among the wicked, but sufficient is your Lord as a Guide and Helper"
  25,32,"The disbelievers say, ‚ÄúIf only the Quran had been sent down to him all at once!‚ÄĚ ňĻWe have sent itňļ as such ňĻin stagesňļ so We may reassure your heart with it. And We have revealed it at a deliberate pace"
  25,33,"Whenever they bring you an argument, We come to you with the right refutation and the best explanation"
  25,34,"Those who will be dragged into Hell on their faces will be in the worst place, and are ňĻnowňļ farthest from the ňĻRightňļ Way"
  25,35,We certainly gave Moses the Book and appointed his brother Aaron as his helper
  25,36,"We had ordered ňĻthemňļ, ‚ÄúGo to the people who would deny Our signs.‚ÄĚ Then We annihilated the deniers entirely"
  25,37,"And when the people of Noah rejected the messengers,¬†We drowned them, making them an example to humanity. And We have prepared a painful punishment for the wrongdoers"
  25,38,"Also ňĻWe destroyedňļ ‚Äô»ād, Tham√Ľd, and the people of the Water-pit,¬†as well as many peoples in between"
  25,39,"For each We set forth ňĻvariousňļ lessons, and We ultimately destroyed each"
  25,40,"They have certainly passed by the city ňĻof Sodomňļ, which had been showered with a dreadful rain ňĻof stonesňļ. Have they not seen its ruins? But they do not expect to be resurrected"
  25,41,"When they see you ňĻO Prophetňļ, they only make fun of you, ňĻsaying,ňļ ‚ÄúIs this the one that Allah has sent as a messenger"
  25,42,"He would have almost tricked us away from our gods, had we not been so devoted to them.‚ÄĚ ňĻButňļ soon they will know, when they face the punishment, who is far astray from the ňĻRightňļ Way"
  25,43,Have you seen ňĻO Prophetňļ the one who has taken their own desires as their god? Will you then be a keeper over them
  25,44,"Or do you think that most of them listen or understand?¬†They are only like cattle‚ÄĒno, more than that, they are astray from the ňĻRightňļ Way"
  25,45,Have you not seen how your Lord extends the shade‚ÄĒHe could have simply made it ňĻremainňļ still if He so willed‚ÄĒthen We make the sun its guide
  25,46,causing the shade to retreat gradually
  25,47,"He is the One Who has made the night for you as a cover, and ňĻmadeňļ sleep for resting, and the day for rising"
  25,48,"And He is the One Who sends the winds ushering in His mercy, and We send down pure rain from the sky"
  25,49,"giving life to a lifeless land, and providing water for countless animals and humans of Our Own creation"
  25,50,"We certainly disperse it among them so they may be mindful, but most people persist in ungratefulness"
  25,51,"Had We willed, We could have easily sent a warner to every society"
  25,52,"So do not yield to the disbelievers, but strive diligently against them with this ňĻQuranňļ"